item.title: Breaking Down Seahawks 2025 Free Agency
item.itunes:title: Breaking Down Seahawks 2025 Free Agency
item.description:
The Seahawks had a busy start to free agency which included the signing of Pro Bowl quarterback Sam Darnold and agreeing to terms with Super Bowl LVI MVP wide receiver Cooper Kupp. Jen Mueller and John Boyle break down everything you need to know about the Seahawks' 2025 free agency class. Today's show: Roster shakeup (00:48), Excitement around Sam Darnold (02:37), What Darnold learned from the end of last season (07:16), What clicked for Darnold in 2024 (09:58), Kubiak’s system (15:03) and Cooper Kupp (17:20).

See omnystudio.com/listener for privacy information.

item.description:
Former quarterback Sam Adkins joined the show to swap stories with two of his longtime teammates, Jim Zorn and Steve Raible. Today’s show: driving into the stadium with fans (03:20), winning a car (05:13), NFL salaries and food in the ‘70s (06:20), $1,500 hot dog (07:44), crowd noise penalties in the Kingdome (08:21), Howard Mudd’s influence on the game (11:38), Adkins memories of being a Seahawk (17:53), only Seahawk to ever wear the No. 12 jersey (19:39), life after football (24:20), success in 1978 and 1979 seasons (27:11), and fondest memories with the Seahawks (32:41).
